@NODE "What" "What"
@{B}What's Bootmanager ?@{UB}

This is a simple program wich allows you to boot from another startup-sequence
by pressing one of the 10 fkeys or one of the three mouse buttons while booting.
You can execute 13 differents startup-sequence files, depending on wich button
you press. If you press the HELP key, tour startup-sequence will be executed
step by step, very usefull to find a problem :)

If no button are pressed, your startup-sequence will be executed normaly so
your Amiga will boot as usual.
But if you press a button to wich you've assigned another startup file, this last
will be executed while the real startup-sequence won't.

So this is the fastest way to have multi-boot without running a menu or something
else at the boot.

I use it to boot MacOS via Shapeshifter in "quick mode" without loading the WB or booting with
"no startup sequence". By this way, the MacOS boot like if I had a real Mac :)
I use it also to boot linux PPC directly without starting the workbench, thus it look like a real
OS that boot without the help of another OS ! :P

But don't be affraid,
you can boot other things than Shapeshifter or Linux PPC, it's just an exemple ! You can do for
example, different startup file to boot on other hardrive, or to boot a light version of your
startup-sequence to gain memory for games or something else...

@{B}NOTE THAT THIS PROGRAM ONLY WORK WITH A MOUSE CONNECTED TO @{UB}
@{B}THE ORIGINAL AMIGA MOUSE PORT AND HAVE NOT BEEN TESTED WITH@{UB}
@{B}A PC KEYBOARD CONNECTED TO AN ADAPTOR@{UB}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Install" "Install"
@{B}INSTALLATION: VERY EASY !@{UB}

before using BootManager, you must run the "install" script. or copy manually the files.

@{B} I strongly recommend to use the install script, because if you don't want to keep BootManager
on your HardDrive, you will be able to use the "Uninstall" script to remove any trace of this soft
including changes made in your startup-sequence file @{UB}

@{U}BootManager Pref program@{UU}
  
  Well it's quite easy, just select the file you want to assign in the corresponding
  popGadget that represents F keys and mouse buttons.

  For exemple, if you want to assign a startup to the left mouse button, clik on the gadget
  button "Left Mouse Button".
  Then click "SAVE" (or select other file for other button). Now, when you will reboot,
  if you press the left Mouse button (keep it pushed until your file is launched) the
  file you've selected will be executed (and startup-sequence will be alted). Else, your
  startup-sequence will be executed normaly.

  To remove performed changes simply run the "Uninstall" script (exept if you have not used the install script)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Req" "requierment"
@{B}Requierments@{UB}:

- An Amiga with an hard drive (this program is not very usefull without an hardrive !)
- MUI 3.8 is needed for the prefs program (not tested on earlier versions)
- The main program should work on any version of the Workbench

BootManager was tested on:
    - Amiga 4000 PPC 200Mhz/060, 128 Mb, Rom 3.1 Wb 3.9, Mui 3.8 (with a Mroocheck adaptor and a PC mouse)
    - Amiga 1200 030 50 Mhz, 8 Mb, Rom 3.0, WB 3.1, Mui 3.8

@ENDNODE
