@ENDNODE
@NODE "Faq" "FAQ"
@{B}Frequently Asked Questions@{UB}

@{B}Q: I press a mouse button on startup, but nothing change, why ?@{UB}

A: On Some setup,you will need to wait until IDE disks are initialised (after the led flashed) before
   pressing any key or mouse button.


@{B}Q: I have a startup file on another drive which I want to noot from
   like if it was the main boot disk, but it does not do exactly what
   I expeted.
@{UB}
A: When BootManager detect the pressed key, the normal boot partition has
   already booted.So the Amiga OS has already assign SYS: to that partition.
   If you want to make the partition that contain your startup-file to become
   SYS: you have to add this line in the begining of the file:

   Assign SYS: Your_Partition:

@ENDNODE
